{"id":1026343498,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"2 months, 4 weeks","timestamp":1692502613,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1415 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1026343498/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Maximize the Profit as the Salesman","memory":"70.4 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def maximizeTheProfit(self, n, offers):\n        offers.sort(key=lambda x: x[1])\n\n        arr = [0] * n\n        oI = 0\n\n        for i in range(n):\n            arr[i] = arr[i - 1] if i > 0 else 0\n            \n            while oI < len(offers) and offers[oI][1] == i:\n                start = offers[oI][0]\n                gold = offers[oI][2]\n                arr[i] = max(arr[i], (arr[start - 1] if start > 0 else 0) + gold)\n                oI += 1\n\n        return arr[n - 1]\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"maximize-the-profit-as-the-salesman","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
